<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>SPA test application</title>
	<style>
		.completed {
			color: maroon;
			text-decoration: line-through;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<h1>{{value: HeaderText}}</h1>

		<fieldset>
			<label></label>

      <p>The generated links use so called hashbang (<code>#!</code>) notation to allow Googlebot to index pages fetched using AJAX.</p>
      <p>Google Bot will request the pages using a special URLs containing <code>_escaped_fragment_</code> query with encoded original fragment (<code>#</code>).</p>
      <p>The server must be ready to handle <code>_escaped_fragment_</code> URLs and server content for the crawler corresponding to what a visitor would receive on that URL.</p>
      <p>More info on the matter for making AJAX SPAs crawlable at <a href="https://developers.google.com/webmasters/ajax-crawling/docs/getting-started">Google Developers</a>.</p>

			<ul>
				<li>
          <rw:RouteLink RouteName="Sample17" Param-Id="16" Text="Sample 1" />
          <a href="/Sample17/14?_escaped_fragment_=/Sample17/16">(+ what Google Bot would request for that link)</a>
        </li>
				<li>
          <rw:RouteLink RouteName="Sample17_B" Text="Sample 2 - Task List" />
          <a href="/Sample17_B?_escaped_fragment_=/Sample17_B">(+ what Google Bot would request for that link)</a>
        </li>
			</ul>

		</fieldset>
	
		<rw:SpaContentPlaceHolder ID="MainContent" />
	
		<rw:RequiredResource Name="bootstrap" />
	</div>
</body>
</html>